verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho, saying,

verses.text_plain: Command the children of Israel, that they give unto the Levites of the inheritance of their possession cities to dwell in; and ye shall give also unto the Levites suburbs for the cities round about them.
verses.verse_html: 2Command the children of Israel, that they give unto the Levites of the inheritance of their possession cities to dwell in; and ye shall give also unto the Levites suburbs for the cities round about them.

verses.text_plain: And the cities shall they have to dwell in; and the suburbs of them shall be for their cattle, and for their goods, and for all their beasts.
verses.verse_html: 3And the cities shall they have to dwell in; and the suburbs of them shall be for their cattle, and for their goods, and for all their beasts.

tokens.text: shall they have to dwell in
of them shall be for their cattle

verses.text_plain: And the suburbs of the cities, which ye shall give unto the Levites, shall reach from the wall of the city and outward a thousand cubits round about.
verses.verse_html: 4And the suburbs of the cities, which ye shall give unto the Levites, shall reach from the wall of the city and outward a thousand cubits round about.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall measure from without the city on the east side two thousand cubits, and on the south side two thousand cubits, and on the west side two thousand cubits, and on the north side two thousand cubits; and the city shall be in the midst: this shall be to them the suburbs of the cities.
verses.verse_html: 5And ye shall measure from without the city on the east side two thousand cubits, and on the south side two thousand cubits, and on the west side two thousand cubits, and on the north side two thousand cubits; and the city shall be in the midst: this shall be to them the suburbs of the cities.

tokens.text: this shall be to them the suburbs

verses.text_plain: And among the cities which ye shall give unto the Levites there shall be six cities for refuge, which ye shall appoint for the manslayer, that he may flee thither: and to them ye shall add forty and two cities.
verses.verse_html:
6And among the cities which ye shall give unto the Levites there shall be six cities for refuge, which ye shall appoint for the manslayer, that he may flee thither: and to them ye shall add forty and two cities.
 to them: Heb. above them ye shall give

tokens.text: thither: and to them ye shall add

footnotes.body_text: to them: Heb. above them ye shall give
footnotes.body_html: to them: Heb. above them ye shall give

verses.text_plain: So all the cities which ye shall give to the Levites shall be forty and eight cities: them shall ye give with their suburbs.
verses.verse_html: 7So all the cities which ye shall give to the Levites shall be forty and eight cities: them shall ye give with their suburbs.

verses.text_plain: And the cities which ye shall give shall be of the possession of the children of Israel: from them that have many ye shall give many; but from them that have few ye shall give few: every one shall give of his cities unto the Levites according to his inheritance which he inheriteth.
verses.verse_html:
8And the cities which ye shall give shall be of the possession of the children of Israel: from them that have many ye shall give many; but from them that have few ye shall give few: every one shall give of his cities unto the Levites according to his inheritance which he inheriteth.
 he: Heb. they inherit

footnotes.body_html: he: Heb. they inherit

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 9And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye be come over Jordan into the land of Canaan;
verses.verse_html: 10Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye be come over Jordan into the land of Canaan;

tokens.text: unto them, When ye be come over

verses.text_plain: Then ye shall appoint you cities to be cities of refuge for you; that the slayer may flee thither, which killeth any person at unawares.
verses.verse_html:
11Then ye shall appoint you cities to be cities of refuge for you; that the slayer may flee thither, which killeth any person at unawares.
 at: Heb. by error

footnotes.body_html: at: Heb. by error

verses.text_plain: And they shall be unto you cities for refuge from the avenger; that the manslayer die not, until he stand before the congregation in judgment.
verses.verse_html: 12And they shall be unto you cities for refuge from the avenger; that the manslayer die not, until he stand before the congregation in judgment.

tokens.text: And they shall be unto you cities

verses.text_plain: And of these cities which ye shall give six cities shall ye have for refuge.
verses.verse_html: 13And of these cities which ye shall give six cities shall ye have for refuge.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall give three cities on this side Jordan, and three cities shall ye give in the land of Canaan, which shall be cities of refuge.
verses.verse_html: 14Ye shall give three cities on this side Jordan, and three cities shall ye give in the land of Canaan, which shall be cities of refuge.

verses.text_plain: These six cities shall be a refuge, both for the children of Israel, and for the stranger, and for the sojourner among them: that every one that killeth any person unawares may flee thither.
verses.verse_html: 15These six cities shall be a refuge, both for the children of Israel, and for the stranger, and for the sojourner among them: that every one that killeth any person unawares may flee thither.

tokens.text: them: that every one that killeth

verses.text_plain: And if he smite him with an instrument of iron, so that he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.
verses.verse_html: 16And if he smite him with an instrument of iron, so that he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.

verses.text_plain: And if he smite him with throwing a stone, wherewith he may die, and he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.
verses.verse_html:
17And if he smite him with throwing a stone, wherewith he may die, and he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.
 with: Heb. with a stone of the hand

footnotes.body_text: with: Heb. with a stone of the hand
footnotes.body_html: with: Heb. with a stone of the hand

verses.text_plain: Or if he smite him with an hand weapon of wood, wherewith he may die, and he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.
verses.verse_html: 18Or if he smite him with an hand weapon of wood, wherewith he may die, and he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.

verses.text_plain: The revenger of blood himself shall slay the murderer: when he meeteth him, he shall slay him.
verses.verse_html: 19The revenger of blood himself shall slay the murderer: when he meeteth him, he shall slay him.

verses.text_plain: But if he thrust him of hatred, or hurl at him by laying of wait, that he die;
verses.verse_html: 20But if he thrust him of hatred, or hurl at him by laying of wait, that he die;

tokens.text: at him by laying of wait

verses.text_plain: Or in enmity smite him with his hand, that he die: he that smote him shall surely be put to death; for he is a murderer: the revenger of blood shall slay the murderer, when he meeteth him.
verses.verse_html: 21Or in enmity smite him with his hand, that he die: he that smote him shall surely be put to death; for he is a murderer: the revenger of blood shall slay the murderer, when he meeteth him.

verses.text_plain: But if he thrust him suddenly without enmity, or have cast upon him any thing without laying of wait,
verses.verse_html: 22But if he thrust him suddenly without enmity, or have cast upon him any thing without laying of wait,

verses.text_plain: Or with any stone, wherewith a man may die, seeing him not, and cast it upon him, that he die, and was not his enemy, neither sought his harm:
verses.verse_html: 23Or with any stone, wherewith a man may die, seeing him not, and cast it upon him, that he die, and was not his enemy, neither sought his harm:

verses.text_plain: Then the congregation shall judge between the slayer and the revenger of blood according to these judgments:
verses.verse_html: 24Then the congregation shall judge between the slayer and the revenger of blood according to these judgments:

verses.text_plain: And the congregation shall deliver the slayer out of the hand of the revenger of blood, and the congregation shall restore him to the city of his refuge, whither he was fled: and he shall abide in it unto the death of the high priest, which was anointed with the holy oil.
verses.verse_html: 25And the congregation shall deliver the slayer out of the hand of the revenger of blood, and the congregation shall restore him to the city of his refuge, whither he was fled: and he shall abide in it unto the death of the high priest, which was anointed with the holy oil.

verses.text_plain: But if the slayer shall at any time come without the border of the city of his refuge, whither he was fled;
verses.verse_html: 26But if the slayer shall at any time come without the border of the city of his refuge, whither he was fled;

verses.text_plain: And the revenger of blood find him without the borders of the city of his refuge, and the revenger of blood kill the slayer; he shall not be guilty of blood:
verses.verse_html:
27And the revenger of blood find him without the borders of the city of his refuge, and the revenger of blood kill the slayer; he shall not be guilty of blood:
 he: Heb. no blood shall be to him

tokens.text: he shall not be guilty of blood

footnotes.body_text: he: Heb. no blood shall be to him
footnotes.body_html: he: Heb. no blood shall be to him

verses.text_plain: Because he should have remained in the city of his refuge until the death of the high priest: but after the death of the high priest the slayer shall return into the land of his possession.
verses.verse_html: 28Because he should have remained in the city of his refuge until the death of the high priest: but after the death of the high priest the slayer shall return into the land of his possession.

verses.text_plain: So these things shall be for a statute of judgment unto you throughout your generations in all your dwellings.
verses.verse_html: 29So these things shall be for a statute of judgment unto you throughout your generations in all your dwellings.

verses.text_plain: Whoso killeth any person, the murderer shall be put to death by the mouth of witnesses: but one witness shall not testify against any person to cause him to die.
verses.verse_html: 30Whoso killeth any person, the murderer shall be put to death by the mouth of witnesses: but one witness shall not testify against any person to cause him to die.

verses.text_plain: Moreover ye shall take no satisfaction for the life of a murderer, which is guilty of death: but he shall be surely put to death.
verses.verse_html:
31Moreover ye shall take no satisfaction for the life of a murderer, which is guilty of death: but he shall be surely put to death.
 guilty: Heb. faulty to die

footnotes.body_html: guilty: Heb. faulty to die

verses.text_plain: And ye shall take no satisfaction for him that is fled to the city of his refuge, that he should come again to dwell in the land, until the death of the priest.
verses.verse_html: 32And ye shall take no satisfaction for him that is fled to the city of his refuge, that he should come again to dwell in the land, until the death of the priest.

verses.text_plain: So ye shall not pollute the land wherein ye are: for blood it defileth the land: and the land cannot be cleansed of the blood that is shed therein, but by the blood of him that shed it.
verses.verse_html:
33So ye shall not pollute the land wherein ye are: for blood it defileth the land: and the land cannot be cleansed of the blood that is shed therein, but by the blood of him that shed it.
 the land cannot: Heb. there can be no expiation for the land

footnotes.body_text: the land cannot: Heb. there can be no expiation for the land
footnotes.body_html: the land cannot: Heb. there can be no expiation for the land

verses.text_plain: Defile not therefore the land which ye shall inhabit, wherein I dwell: for I the Lord dwell among the children of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 34Defile not therefore the land which ye shall inhabit, wherein I dwell: for I the Lord dwell among the children of Israel.
